# StoneRise Image Generation Rules

Use this when generating any marketing images, product graphics, or visual assets for StoneRise.

## Official Logo — MANDATORY

**Always use the official StoneRise logo from:** `Marketing/Brand/stonerise-logo.png`

The logo consists of:
- Three overlapping chevron/arrow shapes (green, teal, blue) pointing right
- "STONERISE" wordmark below in green

**Logo usage:**
- Place in bottom-right corner, outside main content/cards
- Keep small but clearly visible
- Generous padding/whitespace around it
- Never distort, recolour, or add effects
- Never invent or generate a different logo

---

## Image Types

### Type 1: Paid Ad Creatives

For Meta, LinkedIn, or display ads with promotional intent.

**Include:**
- Bold headline (problem-first, per messaging canvas)
- CTA button or prompt
- Strong visual metaphor or attention-grabbing imagery
- StoneRise logo

**Style:** Dark/dramatic backgrounds acceptable, high contrast, direct messaging

### Type 2: Organic LinkedIn Graphics (Founder/Employee Posts)

For product updates, feature showcases, thought leadership visuals.

**Must NOT look like an ad:**
- No big headlines or CTA buttons
- No "Book a demo" or promotional badges
- Product illustration style, not advertisement

**Two sub-styles available:**

#### Style A — Polished Screenshot (Browser Frame)
- UI inside clean browser/app window frame (rounded corners, traffic-light dots)
- Soft gradient background behind frame
- Logo small, outside the frame

#### Style B — Conceptual Floating UI (Layered Cards)
- Multiple UI cards floating and overlapping
- No browser frame — elements float freely
- Varied card angles (mix left tilt, right tilt, flat)
- Soft shadows creating depth layers
- Stat call-outs, progress indicators, mini charts

---

## Style B Layout Guidelines (Floating UI)

### Composition Variance
- **Vary card angles:** Some tilted left, some right, some nearly flat
- **Vary card sizes:** Mix large panels, medium cards, small accent badges
- **Asymmetrical layouts:** Avoid uniform grid arrangements
- **Overlapping:** Cards should overlap to create depth
- **Visual flow:** Arrange cards to suggest a process or workflow where relevant

### Background Options (rotate to avoid repetition)
- Off-white to pale blue-green gradient + dotted grid
- Off-white to warm grey + subtle flowing curves
- Off-white to pale lavender + diagonal lines
- Light neutral to soft teal + abstract shapes

### Card Types to Include
- Data tables (status, amounts, categories)
- Stat call-outs ("75%", "30 sec", "£2.1M")
- Progress rings or bars
- Mini charts (bar, donut, line)
- Workflow node snippets
- Status/alert badges
- Process flow diagrams

---

## Colour Palette

| Use | Colour | Hex |
|-----|--------|-----|
| Primary accent / success | StoneRise Green | #00A86B |
| Secondary accent / UI | StoneRise Blue | #1E5AA8 |
| Warnings / review items | Amber | #F59E0B |
| Error / critical | Red | #EF4444 |
| Backgrounds | Light neutrals | Off-white, pale grey, soft gradients |
| Text | Dark navy/charcoal | #1E293B |

---

## Typography & Legibility

- All text must be readable at LinkedIn mobile feed size (~1080×1080 displayed at ~500px)
- Minimum effective font size ~14px at final resolution
- Use clean sans-serif fonts
- High contrast between text and background

---

## Content Accuracy

- **Keep UI truthful:** Preserve the feature/flow shown in source screenshots
- **Don't invent stats:** Only use approved proof points from the messaging canvas, or stats explicitly provided in post copy
- **Match post content:** Graphics should reflect the key points from the accompanying LinkedIn post

---

## Reference Images

When generating, always include these as reference:
1. `Marketing/Brand/stonerise-logo.png` — for correct logo
2. Previous generated images in the same style (for visual consistency)
3. Any source screenshots provided by the user

---

## Checklist Before Generating

- [ ] Official StoneRise logo will be included (bottom-right, outside content)
- [ ] Image type identified (paid ad vs organic)
- [ ] Style identified (browser frame vs floating UI)
- [ ] Background style chosen (vary from recent images)
- [ ] Card angles varied (not all same tilt)
- [ ] Content matches post copy / feature being showcased
- [ ] Colours match brand palette
